name: tessera
audience: public
description: >
  Self-Validating Executable Document Format. Cryptographic integrity,
  structural validation, thin logic layer. Cheaters can cheat but they
  can't hide it. Data layer with integrity guarantees, not an application runtime.

domains:
  - cryptography
  - privacy
  - document-format
  - hash-chain
  - self-validating

voice:
  tone: precise, minimal, structural
  principles:
    - The document proves itself — no external authority consulted
    - Integrity is detectable, not preventable
    - The engine is a data layer, not an application server
    - Schema declares rules, engine enforces them, application owns the logic
  anti-patterns:
    - Building an application runtime when a data layer suffices
    - Preventing invalid states instead of making them detectable
    - Coupling presentation logic to the integrity layer
    - Over-engineering the logic layer beyond API-gateway complexity

standards:
  code_review:
    - Every mutation in the chain must be independently verifiable
    - Determinism is non-negotiable — same inputs, same result, every platform
    - No floating point in the logic layer
    - Crypto operations use audited libraries only (dalek, sha2)
  documentation:
    - Format spec (SPEC.md) is the source of truth
    - Threat model included for every validation claim
    - Test vectors shared across all future SDK implementations

connects_to:
  - signet
  - blinddb
  - agent-safe
  - kindex
